   <indicator ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output Indicator</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Availability of  monitoring and evaluation framework for implementation of the National Human Rights Action Plan, strengthened coordination role of the Ministry of Justice and enhanced capacity of the relevant stakeholders
2. Improvement of legal framework on torture prevention in line with  the UN Convention against Torture
3. Strengthened role of Ombudsman to implement its mandate as the National Preventive Mechanism and work together with the civil society
4. Availability of policy and legal framework (Criminal Code, Criminal Procedure Code, etc) enabling audio-visual recording of interrogations and introduction of e-protocol system in 10 police detention centres
5. Number of trained police officers conducting interviews/interrogations in line with  the international requirements 
6. Conducive environment for the adoption of the Law on Anti-discrimination, raised public awareness on the issue and strengthened capacity of the relevant stakeholders to deal with the cases of discrimination.</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2017">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Human Rights Action Plan for 2017-2019 prepared yet with the need strong results-based and monitoring and evaluation system to be developed in addition (2017)
2. Partial (2017)
3. The NPM expert council is established, the cooperation with the public monitoring boards is limited (2017)
4. Not available (2017)
5. 0 (2017)
6. General legal provisions on prohibition of discrimination envisaged by the RA Constitution, no separate law (2017)</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2019-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2019-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Provide expert support to the Coordination Council for effective and regular assessment and feedback in terms of development of the new HR Strategy and Action Plan. Provide training sessions for the NA on HR framework and raise public awareness in the field. 
2. Development of the legal frameworks and Standard Operational Procedures stipulating the procedures for conducting audio-visual recording of police interviews. Conduct review of the current legislative provisions. 
3. Strengthening the capacity of the HRDO to act as the National Preventive Mechanism, through provision of expert advice and development of the NPM standards. 
4. On-the-job training for the police officers at 10 pilot police stations on audio-visual recording procedures. Follow up and assess the work of 10 PPS, develop a report with findings and recommendations for improvement for a fully functional audio-visual recording procedure including future actions. 
5. Development and implementation of the communications strategy and Action Plan on anti-discrimination, support to the Equality Body, review of the current Human Rights and Gender modules for the civil servants.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Expert support provided to the Coordination Council for effective and regular assessment and feedback in terms of development of the new HR Strategy and Action Plan. 
2. Legal frameworks and Standard Operational Procedures stipulating the procedures for conducting audio-visual recording of police interviews were developed. legislative provisions are amended and adopted by the National Assembly.
3. Capacity building trainings for HRDO to act as the National Preventive Mechanism were conducted. NPM Standard were developed, translated into English.
4. Training for the police officers of 10 pilot police stations on audio-visual recording procedures were conducted.
5. Communications strategy and Action Plan on anti-discrimination was developed and the implementation was started.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2020-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2020-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Support the Police in implementation of the audio-visual recordings of the police interviews and raise public awareness on legal provisions;
2. Capacitate the Police Educational Complex for conduct of ToT and trainings for the new patrol service officers;
3. Capacitate the MoJ with tools for M&amp;E of the Human Rights Action Plan;
4. Support the HRDO to effectively follow up on implementation of the NPM recommendations.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. The legal amendments on audio-visual recordings of the police interviews drafted with Project&#x2019;s support came into force in January 2020. As a result, the corresponding set-up has been launched in 10 pilot police stations since May 2020. PSA and information leaflet development process launched aimed at raising public awareness on the corresponding legal provisions and the rights of the parties to the process (to be ready by the end of the year).
2. The Project participated in the selection panel for the trainers to provide trainings for the new patrol police officers. As a result, 140 trainers identified; ToT on Human Rights mainstreaming in policing delivered by a Project&#x2019;s commissioned international trainer for 140 trainers; online test for the candidates for the patrol police stations developed and successfully tested.
3. Online HRAP reporting platform www.e-rights.am aimed at improved M&amp;E over the HRAP developed and launched in March 2020 ( ENG/ARM). A PSA on HRAP online platform developed that raised public awareness on the main functions and tools of the platform and facilitated further usage.
4. A chatbot and HR caf&#xE9; with the Human Rights Defender organized, aimed at raising awareness on the mandate of the NPM and the activities of the office (ENG/ARM). NPM standards presented to serve as a practical guide (ENG/ARM). In response to COVID-19 emergency procurement of personal protective equipment for the NPM ensured resulting in uninterrupted visits to closed institutions and follow up on implementation of the recommendations. A series of meetings conducted with the Armenian NPM put the basis for a research and development of an online tool to be conducted through the second phase of the Project in 2021.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
